{
  "title": "Type-Checking Serverless Handlers with FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "Learn how to leverage the power of FastAPI and Python 3.12+ for type-checking your serverless handlers, ensuring robustness and maintaining code consistency.",
  "key_points": [
    "Use FastAPI for building APIs with built-in support for type validation",
    "Ensure that input and output data are of the correct type when handling requests",
    "Leverage Python 3.12+ features such as type hints, type variances, and improved type checking",
    "Create serverless functions with enhanced reliability by catching type errors before deployment"
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "from fastapi import FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\n@app.post('/items/')\ndef create_item(item: dict):\n    return item"
    },
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "import typing\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, Request\n\ndef main(request: Request) -> dict:\n    query_params = request.query_params\n    data = {\n        'item_name': query_params.get(\'item_name\', typ=str),\n        'description': query_params.get(\'description\', typ=str, required=False)\n    }\n    return data"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for improved type checking.",
    "FastAPI 0.74.0 or later is recommended for better integration with Python's type hints."
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "While FastAPI offers robust type-checking, remember that it does not guarantee runtime type validation in all scenarios (e.g., malicious input or user errors).",
    "Ensure to test your functions thoroughly and implement security measures to protect against unintended behavior."
  ]
}
